1
00:01:04,959 --> 00:01:05,489
Captain.

2
00:01:07,440 --> 00:01:08,080
Jingchi.

3
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:10,170
Why are you here?

4
00:01:10,360 --> 00:01:11,960
Do you need me for something?

5
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:13,250
I want to talk to you.

6
00:01:18,440 --> 00:01:18,840
Okay.

7
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:22,450
Go ahead.

8
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:24,740
What do you want to talk about?

9
00:01:26,320 --> 00:01:26,850
Captain.

10
00:01:28,520 --> 00:01:30,850
About me driving a fake car five years ago,

11
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,200
do you still hate me now?

12
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:37,000
It's been five years.

13
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:39,380
Things between us should be settled.

14
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:40,090
Go ahead.

15
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:49,539
That year, my mom got sick.

16
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:54,740
She needed a lot of money for surgery.

17
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:58,610
That's when Suzuki Shota found me.

18
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:01,610
He said he could provide the money.

19
00:02:03,440 --> 00:02:04,040
Jing Chi.

20
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:05,520
You are my teammate.

21
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:07,720
Why didn't you tell me you needed money?

22
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:09,280
Do you still consider me your captain?

23
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:11,680
I was inferior to you in every way back then.

24
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:14,450
I always wanted to surpass you.

25
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:18,020
I didn't want to be looked down upon by everyone.

26
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:26,650
That's true.

27
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:28,760
I was too competitive

28
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,920
and loved showing off back then.

29
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:33,520
I didn't notice your difficulties.

30
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:35,579
Thinking about it now,

31
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:37,760
I was quite stupid back then.

32
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:40,300
I didn't even know I was being harmed.

33
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:43,760
How is your mother doing now?

34
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:46,800
Not very well.

35
00:02:48,079 --> 00:02:50,740
She has to take medicine every day to stay alive.

36
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:52,640
When we have time,

37
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:54,200
take me to see her.

38
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:56,640
She is not in the country.

39
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:57,760
She is abroad.

40
00:02:58,040 --> 00:02:58,640
Abroad?

41
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:01,640
Yes.

42
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:05,360
That is why

43
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,980
I acknowledged Shi Chen as my godfather.

44
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:11,960
You mean

45
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,040
your mother has survived until now

46
00:03:14,040 --> 00:03:16,300
entirely because Mr. Shi is helping you?

47
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:17,960
Yes.

48
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:26,329
Don't be too sad.

49
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:30,360
What happened five years ago

50
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:33,260
is wiped clean.

51
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:40,890
Thank you, Captain.

52
00:03:57,079 --> 00:03:57,360
[Message·RCS]

53
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:57,440
[Message-RCS]

54
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:58,680
I found some clues.

55
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:00,850
Let's talk at the bar tomorrow.

56
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:14,920
Miss Suzuki Yoshiko,

57
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,529
why are you drinking alone?

58
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:19,890
Want me to find a handsome guy to keep you company?

59
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:22,410
I don't think I ordered an escort service.

60
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:23,640
I have some intel

61
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:26,380
you'll definitely be interested in.

62
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:27,640
What intel?

63
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:31,440
The car that killed your brother

64
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,060
appeared there right at that moment.

65
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,200
Do you think it's a coincidence?

66
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:37,560
What do you mean?

67
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:42,250
That car crash wasn't an accident.

68
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,480
It was orchestrated by He Nan.

69
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:47,120
He Nan killed my brother.

70
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:49,120
Didn't expect that, huh?

71
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:51,120
And the current Gu Haoran

72
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:54,440
is actually He Nan in disguise.

73
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:57,780
Is the information reliable?

74
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:01,280
When has my information ever been unreliable?

75
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:06,720
He Nan,

76
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:09,610
I will kill you with my own hands

77
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:11,240
to avenge Shota.

78
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:16,000
Rumor has it that Boss Ye's information

79
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,080
isn't free.

80
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:18,560
Tell me,

81
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:19,880
how much is it?

82
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:20,760
Miss Suzuki,

83
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:23,200
This information...

84
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:26,120
Free.

85
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:32,640
It seems Boss Ye wants to exchange conditions.

86
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:36,480
I really can't hide anything from Miss Suzuki.

87
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:38,200
It's simple.

88
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:40,720
One of my guests

89
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:42,920
also wants him dead.

90
00:05:45,159 --> 00:05:47,080
So you want to use me to kill him.

91
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,360
Of course.

92
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:50,040
You can also refuse.

93
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:53,720
But if you kill He Nan yourself,

94
00:05:55,159 --> 00:05:56,960
wouldn't it be more satisfying?

95
00:05:58,320 --> 00:05:59,040
Okay.

96
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:00,920
Deal.

97
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:21,880
Why?

98
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:23,520
I just feel like the two of them

99
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:25,650
seem really familiar with each other.

100
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:49,360
This guy is the one who used to race dirty

101
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:51,159
and betrayed his teammates, Jingchi.

102
00:06:51,159 --> 00:06:51,800
A few years ago, he went abroad.

103
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:52,600
Jingchi

104
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:54,290
got a new identity and name.

105
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:56,960
So Vincent's real name is Jingchi.

106
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:06,640
Jingchi was in the Jiangnan Team.

107
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,810
My sister also knew the Jiangnan Team.

108
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:24,120
Five years ago.

109
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:28,370
My sister also passed away five years ago.

110
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:29,840
Could it be...

111
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:51,570
When did you learn how to drift?

112
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,120
Just now.

113
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:55,360
Gu Haoran.

114
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:58,800
How did your driving skills suddenly get so good?

115
00:07:58,800 --> 00:07:59,760
It's only been a few days,

116
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:02,420
but you're like a completely different person.

117
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:05,240
Your sister passed away five years ago.

118
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:06,000
I know.

119
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:08,120
She was a great girl.

120
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:11,880
Why is it him?

121
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:13,600
He Nan.

122
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:15,880
You still dare to show your face?

123
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,040
He's not Gu Haoran.

124
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:26,800
He's He Nan.

125
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:33,240
Boss Ye,

126
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:34,169
I'm here.

127
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:39,200
Where are you?

128
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:51,600
This isn't another setup, is it?

129
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:53,160
Relax.

130
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:54,640
The same thing

131
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:56,640
won't happen twice in my bar.

132
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,120
Come on up.

133
00:08:58,640 --> 00:08:59,160
Boss Ye,

134
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,850
so you're upstairs.

135
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:16,640
Boss Ye.

136
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:19,680
Boss Ye, sorry.

137
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:20,720
Don't go.

138
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:23,010
I need you right now.

139
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:25,880
Boss Ye,

140
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:27,480
what is it?

141
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:30,180
Pour me a glass of red wine.

142
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,850
That's not appropriate, is it?

143
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:36,820
You begged me to gather intel for you.

144
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:39,800
You wouldn't refuse this little favor, would you?

145
00:09:56,560 --> 00:09:57,920
You don't have to do this.

146
00:09:57,920 --> 00:09:59,000
I'm in the water.

147
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:02,250
I usually wear more revealing clothes than this.

148
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:06,170
Careful not to fall.

149
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:50,480
Handsome boy.

150
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:51,720
Are you okay?

151
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:54,440
I told you to be careful.

152
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:05,580
Your nose is bleeding.

153
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,800
Let me wipe it for you.

154
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,400
Let me wipe it for you.

155
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:11,240
Boss Ye.

156
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:13,880
Please respect yourself.

157
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:14,280
I...

158
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:16,120
Calling me Boss Ye is too formal.

159
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:18,140
Call me Sister Lan.

160
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:20,440
Okay.

161
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:21,240
Sister Lan.
